A jump map I made with a cliff/ Aztec theme.
This map took me a wile but when finished I was really happy with the results.

This map is not a vain-busting jump map where you will go completely insane over a jump, instead, It is a casual stride map where you can sit back, and enjoy a nice 30 minute jump with friends.

When you get to the top, you can pick up your well earned scout and grenade and if you want, you can go to the extra jump room i included while waiting on others to finish, once done with that, you will be teleported on the cliffs to watch over the map.

I hope you have as much fun as I did making this.

Special thanks to Doomsday and Frosty for helping to test this map.

Info:
This is a big map with multiple sections.There are four secret rooms, each room contains one piece of the code. The order of the rooms is the same as the order of the code. You will need that code to open secret rooms at the end of the map. There is also another secret room sealed with 2 doors,each door can be destroyed by searching the end area for wooden X signs and shooting them(They are not so obvious so good luck finding them). There is also a demo of the cube in the map which is not so easily reachable. The cube is actually a room where you need to climb to a specific area and the whole cube will rotate for 90 degrees and make new obstacle to climb on. In the next map the cube will have many more levels.good luck and hope you will enjoy this map.

April 7, 2011 - V2 Released, changelog below This is my first map, a climb built over the citadel map from HL2, because I decided that I wanted a map with more of a context than just floating platforms.
I learned a lot from building over an existing map (especially one by Valve) enabling me to make major extensions to it whilst preserving the visual and structural style of the combine citadel.

This map includes soundscapes, custom sounds and custom textures, so make sure to keep the bsp named as it should be.

v2 changes
- Fixed being able to get on top of the little concrete surf
- Fixed elevators height glitching after players block them
- Adjusted some steps underneath the huge tilted piece of glass near 2 elevators
- Adjusted the positioning of combine terminals, making them easier to climb
- Adjusted ceiling of an area that players have to crawl through, in case they saved
- Placed playerclip underneath elevators to stop players getting crushed
- Added more arrows
- Added a ladder in case players dropped down to a wrong area and saved
- Removed an unintended step which players could get to
- Added "xc_citadel_01 by Acren" hint
Very fun map, enjoy it!

Cs_StoneTower_V2

This is the second version of the Stone Tower jump map. Its size is absolutely epic, just scraping the surface of the impossible limit of hammer editor's grid. Each screen shot is literally looking at around 1/20th of the entire map. This tower is designed to appeal to the general audience of Counter-Strike: Source, as it is easy to the point of basic skill, yet gets harder as you ascend. It's fun and requires teamwork, precise jumping techniques, and creative thinking. I currently need beta testers and would love to have you try it out. Please assess and provide constructive feedback.

Installing is simple and easy!

1. Open the RAR with a compatible program. (winrar, winzip, etc.)

2. Copy the .bsp file included in the RAR file to C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\SteamApps\common\Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps

3. Click create server and find the map OR open console and type map MG_ClimbingWars and it should show up then click on it and hit enter.
